sif3.infra.common.conversion
Class InfraObjectEnum

java.lang.Object
  sif3.infra.common.conversion.InfraObjectEnum

public class InfraObjectEnum
extends java.lang.Object

Simple enumeration of all valid Infrastructure POJOs that have been generated through JAXB and the Infrastructure XSD. On top of this a hand full of convenience methods are provided to convert an object by its name or a string to an appropriate enumeration value of this class.

Author:
Joerg Huber

getInfraModelEnum

public static InfraObjectEnum.InfraModel getInfraModelEnum(java.lang.String infraModelStr)
Returns the infrastructure enumeration for a given name that should correspond to a name of an Infrastructure POJO as generated by JAXB and the XSD. If the input string does not correspond to any infrastructure POJO name then null is returned. This is a convenience method that deals with error handling instead of having these check all over the higher level code of the framework.

Parameters:
infraModelStr - The name of the POJO class as a string
Returns:
See desc
